d my 9th song and fear that the item might be trivial to me.  I am new to this land but I have fought in similar lands that did not have an issue with trivial loot.  <br><br>First, might someone point this wayward Bard in the right direction to get some information regarding the rules of the land of Firiona Vie?  Especially with the rules regarding Trivial Loot.<br><br>Second, might I get the help of some young adventurers to slay the Large Rattlesnakes for me?<br><br>Thank ye,<br>Xaman<br>Bard of the 9th Song <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uuininstormsong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Uinin Stormsong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 182<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/13/02 9:48:58 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2533.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Preserved Snake Eyes</span><hr size=1> TLC is essentially the Warrens Loot Code on other servers, extended worldwide.<br><br>If an item is MAGIC, and you or someone in your group, receive no experience for killing a critter, then it will not drop that item.  <br><br>Example, if I were to go out and kill a mountain giant hillock carrying a leg-chopper (a magic sword - I can see him carry it), but he's green to me....<br><br>POOF<br><br>Sword will not appear on his body, and I will see a message that reads<br><br>Nyah Nyah!  A_mountain_giant_hillock was a trivial challenge for your party!<br><br>LORE and QUEST items will still appear on corpses and are uunaffected by TLC, unless they also happen to be magic - which is about 95% of the time.<br><br>Can't help you with the second part, but it might behoove you to do a higher-level portion of the quest again (or as much as you can do before the LORE thing kicks in) and offer the semi-completed armor item to a young player in exchange for the eyes.<br><br>Also, scour the vendors in the area.  You'd be amazed at what gets dumped.<br><br>Good luck. <p><div align="center"><b>Uinin Stormsong</b><br>Bard of the Ledenyetz Troupe<br>Herald of Karana<br>~ <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=268592">My Current Playlist</a> ~</div></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utzarothfv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tzaroth FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 91<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/13/02 10:24:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2533.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Preserved Snake Eyes</span><hr size=1> I've seen Large Rattlesnakes in the Northern Desert of Ro pretty frequently. I think they're about sixth level, but I could be easily mistaken. By the sound of the item (Preserved Snake Eyes), it doesn't really sound like something they'd drop. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uuininstormsong.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Uinin Stormsong</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 183<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/13/02 10:52:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2533.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Preserved Snake Eyes</span><hr size=1> Lucky lucky you...<br><br><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/db/quest.html?quest=1827">everquest.allakhazam.com/...quest=1827</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br><br>Turns out the preserved snake eyes drop from Darkweed Snakes in the Commons... decidedly NOT trivial to you at 9.  If you need help, look for a human monk named Dogen (11th), currently swinging with the Halfling hotties in Misty Thicket.<br><br>Good luck. <p><div align="center"><b>Uinin Stormsong</b><br>Bard of the Ledenyetz Troupe<br>Herald of Karana<br>~ <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=268592">My Current Playlist</a> ~</div></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/utzarothfv.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tzaroth FV</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 96<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/13/02 10:53:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2533.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Preserved Snake Eyes</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> ... decidedly NOT trivial to you at 9 ...<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Probably /white or /yellow, actually. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uvallerianwintermyst.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vallerian Wintermyst</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 12<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/13/02 11:17:41 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2533.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Preserved Snake Eyes</span><hr size=1> These people are not really answering your question, so I will.<br>No, you are not too high to recieve this item. You could be level 50 and still get it. It does not fall under the TLC because it is not Magic or Lore.<br><br>Preserved Snake Eyes can be found by killing Darkweed Snakes, not Large or Giant Rattlesnakes. Most of the online documents are wrong by listing the other snakes; but it is Darkweed Snakes that carry these.<br><br>However, at level 9 you will have a hard time killing one of these and even if you do, the poison will likely kill you afterward (it is incredibly potent). I suggest getting a partner to help, perhaps a Mage with a water pet since it is highly resistant to poison.<br><br>Hope that helps.<br><br> <p>--Val<p align="center"><ahref="http://mysite.freeserve.com/Intereo_Liberi/test3.htm"target="_blank"><imgsrc="http://mysite.freeserve.com/Intereo_Liberi/mythresult/phoenix.jpg"border="0" width="330" height="175"></a><br>I took the <ahref="http://mysite.freeserve.com/Intereo_Liberi/test3.htm"target="_blank">What Mythological Creature Are you?</a> test by<lj user=peacefulchaos> !</p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uroque32.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Roque32</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/13/02 12:30:43 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2533.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Preserved Snake Eyes</span><hr size=1> Thank ye all for your aid.  I will brace myself for the upcoming battles with those nasty Darkweed Snakes.<br><br>I am worried now.  Since, I was misinformed regarding the preserved snake eyes.  I fear that I was misinformed regarding the Vial of Smoke.  Do these really fall from Willowisps?<br><br>Xaman<br>Bard of the 9th Song <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucaillougna.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Caillou GNA</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.tshrew.net/caillou/Caillou-sm.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 334<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/13/02 1:17:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2533.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.tshrew.net/caillou/Caillou-sm.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Preserved Snake Eyes</span><hr size=1> Vials of smoke do indeed fall from wisps.  But you need a magic weapon to combat them.  I found a few ((after the patch adding those new quests)) while I was killing wisps to make plat... when I was a lot younger.<br><br>Lightstones (or any type) are a good example of the TLC.  When wisps are green, you can't get the stones.  Get the stones now now now while you are young.<br><br>Do you need a weapon that is magical? <br><br>-Caillou Kyrielle<br>&lt;Saga&gt; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uroque32.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Roque32</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/13/02 2:52:19 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2533.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Preserved Snake Eyes</span><hr size=1> I was actually going to make the run to Katta Kastellum to pickup the song that allows my weapon to hit a magical creature.<br><br>I have made the run in past lives in another land and did not find it too difficult.  Of course, with that Bard I had learned my 26th song so I was much faster.  I have only learned my 9th song so if I were to meet my demise during my dangerous trek, there would be no serious ramifications.  In fact, if I were to successfully purchase the song, my plan is to slap the nearest guard or creature so they can send me home to Freeport <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>'Tis going to be a wonderful adventure <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br>Cheers,<br>Xaman<br>Bard of the 9th Song<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ucylria.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cylria</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 68<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(8/13/02 3:33:46 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2533.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Preserved Snake Eyes</span><hr size=1> Vials of smoke do drop off willowisps, but ONLY the ones in East Commons (they might drop near Qeynos, but I've never seen one drop in West Commons, even after two levels of hunting them there).<br><br>Wisps start to green out at level 16 or so, You've got plenty of time left.<br><br>Since you are near Freeport, instead of making the trip to the moon to get a nearly worthless song, instead make your way to the Eastern wastes. Follow the cliff from the bridge until you find someone hunting Ulthoks, Ry'gor, or Giants. See if they'll sell you a velium weapon. They'll only get a few pp each by selling these to merchants, so you can get these cheap. They are magical and have the same stats as fine steel weapons.<br> <p><html><head><title></title></head><body><img src=http://home.insight.rr.com/cylria/cylriafvrelax.jpg><BR>Cylria Silversong<BR>Minstrel of the Twins<BR>Firiona Vie<BR></body></html></p><i></i></td></tr></ta